atoms.title: How Many Additions
atoms.instructor_notes:
The Russian Peasant Algorithm: 
def russian(a,b):
    x = a; y = b
    z = 0
    while x > 0:
        if x % 2 == 1; z = z + y
        y = y << 1
        x = x >> 1
    return z

atoms.title: Counting Steps
atoms.instructor_notes:
Remember that python uses integer division which means that, for example, 11/5 will return 2, not 2.2. Due to the way pyton does integer division, the code Prof. Littman writes should actually be 
3 + 2 * math.ceil(n/5.0)
